flowRoot.flowPara: With no signal present at the PW MOD input, ,the knob adjusts the pluse waveform's width from 50% (square wave) up to 5%. At higher frequencies the minimum pulse width will go to 0% (no out-put).
Input for exponential pitch control signal with linear adjustable depth control.
Input for exponential pitch control signal with logarithmic adjustable depth control.
Fine tune adjustment from −12 to +12 semitones.
Modulation input for pulse width control. When a signal is present the Pulse Width Control knob, , sets the depth of the pulse width modulation signal.

Sets the synchronization type to Weak (W) or Strong (S). Weak synchronization will force the VCO to lock to interger or fractional multiples of the master frequency, with the reset occuring near the waveform's maximum value. Strong synchronization forces the VCO to reset with every cycle of the master, regardless of where it is in its waveform cycle.
Changes the frequency range in 1 octave steps from +0 octaves to +5 octaves.
